title: Orange & Rosemary Prosciutto-wrapped Grilled Shrimp
summary: Orange & Rosemary Prosciutto-wrapped Grilled Shrimp is a gluten free, dairy free, fodmap friendly, and pescatarian recipe with 24 servings. One portion of this dish contains about 2g of protein, 4g of fat, and a total of 64 calories. For 99 cents per serving, this recipe covers 1% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. If you have rosemary, sambuca liqueur, shrimp, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. 1 person were glad they tried this recipe. It will be a hit at your The Fourth Of July event. It is brought to you by SippitySup. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes approximately 30 minutes. Taking all factors into account, this recipe earns a spoonacular score of 8%, which is very bad (but still fixable). winePairing.pairingText: Pinot Grigio, Riesling, and Sauvignon Blanc are my top picks for Shrimp. These crisp white wines work well with shrimp prepared in a variety of ways, whether grilled, fried, or in garlic sauce. One wine you could try is Alsace Willm Pinot Gris Reserve. It has 4.4 out of 5 stars and a bottle costs about 16 dollars.

productMatches.title: Alsace Willm Pinot Gris Reserve
productMatches.description: An intense golden color with hints of ocher, the wine has a nose of ripe fruit, quince. In the mouth the attack is both supple and full, with notes of honey and spices. The final perfectly balances sugar and acidity.Pair this wine alongside pan-fried foie gras, grilled or roasted white meats (pork, veal), rabbit, poultry in cream sauce, smoked fish, mushroom dishes such as risotto.
